From: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
Date: Tue, 26 Jul 2011 16:08:32 -0700
Subject: coredump: use task comm instead of (unknown)
Git-commit: 3141c8b165644774eb0e83d8330fbe47e45b37bf
Patch-mainline: yes
References: bnc#710868 fate#309473

If we don't know the file corresponding to the binary (i.e.  exe_file is
unknown), use "task->comm (path unknown)" instead of simple "(unknown)"
as suggested by ak.

The fallback is the same as %e except it will append "(path unknown)".

